trans-unit.source: Used to pass a value, or an array of values, to an image encoder.
You can also use an <xref:System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameter> object to receive a list of possible values supported by a particular parameter of a particular image encoder.

Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameter"></xref> class with the specified <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.Encoder"></xref> object and one unsigned 8-bit integer.

Sets the <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameter.ValueType"></xref> property to <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameterValueType.ValueTypeByte"></xref>, and sets the <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameter.NumberOfValues"></xref> property to 1.
An <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.Encoder"></xref> object that encapsulates the globally unique identifier of the parameter category.
An 8-bit unsigned integer that specifies the value stored in the <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameter"></xref> object.

Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameter"></xref> class with the specified <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.Encoder"></xref> object and four arrays of 32-bit integers.
The four arrays represent an array rational ranges.
A rational range is the set of all fractions from a minimum fractional value through a maximum fractional value.
Sets the property to , and sets the property to the number of elements in the numerator1 array, which must be the same as the number of elements in the other three arrays.
The ith range consists of all fractional numbers from numerator1[i]/denominator1[i] through numerator2[i]/denominator2[i].
An <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.Encoder"></xref> object that encapsulates the globally unique identifier of the parameter category.
An array of 32-bit integers that specifies the numerators of the minimum values for the ranges.
The integers in the array must be nonnegative.
An array of 32-bit integers that specifies the denominators of the minimum values for the ranges.
The integers in the array must be nonnegative.
An array of 32-bit integers that specifies the numerators of the maximum values for the ranges.
The integers in the array must be nonnegative.
An array of 32-bit integers that specifies the denominators of the maximum values for the ranges.
The integers in the array must be nonnegative.

Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameter"></xref> class with the specified <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.Encoder"></xref> object and four, 32-bit integers.
The four integers represent a range of fractions.
The first two integers represent the smallest fraction in the range, and the remaining two integers represent the largest fraction in the range.

Sets the <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameter.ValueType"></xref> property to <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameterValueType.ValueTypeRationalRange"></xref>, and sets the <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameter.NumberOfValues"></xref> property to 1.
An <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.Encoder"></xref> object that encapsulates the globally unique identifier of the parameter category.
A 32-bit integer that represents the numerator of the smallest fraction in the range.
Must be nonnegative.
A 32-bit integer that represents the denominator of the smallest fraction in the range.
Must be nonnegative.
A 32-bit integer that represents the denominator of the smallest fraction in the range.
Must be nonnegative.
A 32-bit integer that represents the numerator of the largest fraction in the range.
Must be nonnegative.

Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameter"></xref> class with the specified <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.Encoder"></xref> object and three integers that specify the number of values, the data type of the values, and a pointer to the values stored in the <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameter"></xref> object.
An <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.Encoder"></xref> object that encapsulates the globally unique identifier of the parameter category.
An integer that specifies the number of values stored in the <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameter"></xref> object.
The <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameter.NumberOfValues"></xref> property is set to this value.

A member of the <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameterValueType"></xref> enumeration that specifies the data type of the values stored in the <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameter"></xref> object.
The <xref href="System.Type"></xref> and <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameter.ValueType"></xref> properties are set to this value.
A pointer to an array of values of the type specified by the Type parameter.
Type is not a valid <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameterValueType"></xref>.

Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameter"></xref> class with the specified <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.Encoder"></xref> object, number of values, data type of the values, and a pointer to the values stored in the <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameter"></xref> object.
An <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.Encoder"></xref> object that encapsulates the globally unique identifier of the parameter category.

The <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameter.NumberOfValues"></xref> property is set to this value.

A pointer to an array of values of the type specified by the Type parameter.

Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameter"></xref> class with the specified <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.Encoder"></xref> object and two arrays of 64-bit integers.
The two arrays represent an array integer ranges.
Sets the property to , and sets the property to the number of elements in the rangebegin array, which must be the same as the number of elements in the rangeend array.
An <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.Encoder"></xref> object that encapsulates the globally unique identifier of the parameter category.
An array of 64-bit integers that specifies the minimum values for the integer ranges.
The integers in the array must be nonnegative.
The 64-bit integers are converted to 32-bit integers before they are stored in the <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameter"></xref> object.
An array of 64-bit integers that specifies the maximum values for the integer ranges.
The integers in the array must be nonnegative.
The 64-bit integers are converted to 32-bit integers before they are stored in the <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameters"></xref> object.
A maximum value of a given index is paired with the minimum value of the same index.

Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameter"></xref> class with the specified <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.Encoder"></xref> object and two arrays of 32-bit integers.
The two arrays represent an array of fractions.
Sets the property to , and sets the property to the number of elements in the numerator array, which must be the same as the number of elements in the denominator array.
An <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.Encoder"></xref> object that encapsulates the globally unique identifier of the parameter category.
An array of 32-bit integers that specifies the numerators of the fractions.
The integers in the array must be nonnegative.
An array of 32-bit integers that specifies the denominators of the fractions.
The integers in the array must be nonnegative.
A denominator of a given index is paired with the numerator of the same index.

Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameter"></xref> class with the specified <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.Encoder"></xref> object and a pair of 32-bit integers.
The pair of integers represents a fraction, the first integer being the numerator, and the second integer being the denominator.

Sets the <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameter.ValueType"></xref> property to <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameterValueType.ValueTypeRational"></xref>, and sets the <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameter.NumberOfValues"></xref> property to 1.

The pair of integers represents a range of integers, the first integer being the smallest number in the range, and the second integer being the largest number in the range.

Sets the <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameter.ValueType"></xref> property to <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameterValueType.ValueTypeLongRange"></xref>, and sets the <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameter.NumberOfValues"></xref> property to 1.

This parameter is converted to a 32-bit integer before it is stored in the <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameter"></xref> object.
A 64-bit integer that represents the largest number in a range of integers.
Must be nonnegative.
This parameter is converted to a 32-bit integer before it is stored in the <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameter"></xref> object.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameter"></xref> class with the specified <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.Encoder"></xref> object and one 8-bit value.

Sets the <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameter.ValueType"></xref> property to <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameterValueType.ValueTypeUndefined"></xref> or <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameterValueType.ValueTypeByte"></xref>, and sets the <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameter.NumberOfValues"></xref> property to 1.

The string is converted to a null-terminated ASCII string before it is stored in the <xref href="System.Drawing.Imaging.EncoderParameter"></xref> object.
